def: The room or place where players dress for the stage.
Frowning; scowling. [Obs.]Her frowny mother's ragged shoulder. Sir F. Palgrave.
The bitter principle of wormwood (Artemisia absinthium). Watts.
Partaking of the nature both of vegetable and animal matter; --a term sometimes applied to vegetable albumen and gluten, from theirresemblance to similar animal products.
One of a pair of a paired organs.
The theory that the various forms of activity in nature aremanifestations of the same force. G. H. Lewes.
An improvement of an estate which renders it better than mererepairing would do; -- generally used in the plural. [U. S.] Bouvier.
